parameters.name: TIME_TAG
parameters.description:
A derived value for the timetag associated with the
           x,y,z sample in each record. The derived value is created by the 
           following formula:
           MET + 0.05 * delta_ts + (dt_sample)*(I-1). 
           MET is the mission elapsed time for the entire science packet.
           delta_ts is the delta time in seconds between the MET and
           the first sample in the downloaded science packet.
           dt_sample is the time between samples in seconds and given by 
           dt_sample = 1/sample_rate where sample_rate is the reported 
           sample rate in samples per second.
           I is the incremental counter for each data sample in the
           science packet. I=1 is the first sample in the packet.

parameters.name: DELTA_TS
parameters.description:
The delta time in 50 millisecond steps between the MET  
       value for the packet and the first sample in the science packet,       
       provides a 50 millisecond resolution to the time tag for the first data
       value.

parameters.name: NUM_SAMPLES
parameters.description:
The number of MAG samples (0-200) in the science        
                      packet.

parameters.name: NUM_LOGAC
parameters.description:
The number of logAC samples (0-200) in the              
                      science packet.

parameters.name: COMPRESS_ON
parameters.description:
Indicates whether science packet was compressed or      
                      uncompressed. =0 uncompressed, =1 compressed.

parameters.name: RANGE_MODE
parameters.description: Range control mode used. =0 manual, =1 automatic

parameters.name: FILTERS_ON
parameters.description:
Indicates whether filters were on or off.               
                      =0 off, =1 on

parameters.name: MANUAL_RANGE_CMD
parameters.description:
Commanded manual range setting.                         
                      =0 1530 nT, =1 51300 nT

parameters.name: ACTUAL_RANGE
parameters.description: Actual range used by MAG. =0 1530 nT, =1 51300 nT.

parameters.name: AC_AXIS
parameters.description:
AC axis selected.                                       
                      =0 X, =1 Y, =2 Z

parameters.name: APP_ID
parameters.description:
The Application Process ID of the science packet from   
    which data was extracted. Values for PROBE_TEMPERATURE are N/A when this  
    value is 721, which is the AppID of the old packet format. An AppID of 725
    identifies the new packet format which contains valid values for          
    PROBE_TEMPERATURE.

parameters.name: X_SAMPLES_COMPRESSION_BITS
parameters.description:
Number of bits needed to store each compressed X axis   
    sample.

parameters.name: Y_SAMPLES_COMPRESSION_BITS
parameters.description:
Number of bits needed to store each compressed Y axis   
    sample.

parameters.name: Z_SAMPLES_COMPRESSION_BITS
parameters.description:
Number of bits needed to store each compressed Z axis   
    sample.

parameters.name: PROBE_TEMPERATURE
parameters.description:
Raw telemetry counts of the High temperature resolution 
    probe temperature.This is set to an N/A value of 65535 when APP_ID is 721.
